# Environment Variables Setup Guide

This file contains the required environment variables for the YAH Admin application.
Create a `.env.local` file in the root directory and add these variables:

## Auth0 Configuration
```
AUTH0_SECRET=your-secret-key-here
AUTH0_BASE_URL=https://yah-admin.netlify.app
AUTH0_ISSUER_BASE_URL=https://your-auth0-domain.auth0.com
AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=your-auth0-client-id
AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET=your-auth0-client-secret
```

## Database Configuration (if using)
```
DATABASE_URL=your-database-connection-string
```

## Notes:
- For production deployment on Netlify, add these as environment variables in the Netlify dashboard
- The AUTH0_SECRET should be a random 32-character string
- Make sure AUTH0_BASE_URL matches your deployed URL
- For local development, use http://localhost:3000 as AUTH0_BASE_URL